/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:5:**Inputs:** `*-execution-waves.json` (plan), `*-execution-waves.json.state.json` (state)
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:9:A real-time operational dashboard that compares planned execution (waveplan) against current state and exposes drift, blockers, and the next action within a five-second glance. The panel is not a document viewer; it is the cockpit for the agentic code factory.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:32:9. Color is not decoration. Color is state.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:44:`drift` is an additive flag rendered as an overlay badge; the underlying status remains one of the others. Drift means the actual state diverges from what the plan declared (owner, status, dependencies, or artifacts).
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:100:Motion is reserved for the `running` spinner only. Drift renders as a small purple `git-compare` overlay at the top-right corner of any node card whose actual state diverges from the plan.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:147:| edge state | trigger | color |
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:162:| state | color | dash pattern | weight |
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:179:A single card renders at one of three density tiers based on focus state. Switching tiers must NOT cause swimlane reflow; expansion happens via overlay or scale transform anchored at the card's center.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:252:The drawer is the default surface because the active task answers four of the six glance-questions. Three drawer states exist; the user's choice is persisted across sessions in `localStorage` under `dashboard.drawerState`:
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:256:- **peek** — temporary, mouse-driven. When the drawer is in `collapsed-rail`, hovering the rail or clicking any node expands the drawer over the swimlanes as a 4-column overlay (no layout reflow). Releasing focus or pressing `Escape` collapses back to the rail. Peek does not change the persisted state.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:258:Operators in graph-heavy troubleshooting collapse to the rail once and the dashboard stays out of their way. Operators with a single hot task keep it expanded. Switching states is keyboard-bound (`Ctrl+\` toggles between expanded and rail) and surfaces a 1px caret affordance at the drawer's left edge.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:279:| 4 | `Plan Mismatch` | amber | `state.plan_ref` does not match the loaded plan |
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:314:- Header: task ID, owner pill, status icon + label, primary `Next Action` button (state-driven label such as `Mark verified`, `Unblock`, `Reassign`).
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:320:The Next Action button is the single click that mutates state. It must not encourage premature action when the data backing the recommendation is suspect.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:322:Gating rules — the button enters one of four states based on freshness and integrity:
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:324:| condition | button state | visual |
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:329:| `truth-degraded` OR `Stale` (> 15s) | **locked** | 50% opacity · cursor `not-allowed` · click is a no-op; tooltip reads `state integrity unverified — refresh required` |
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:331:The button label always indicates what the action will do (`Mark verified`), never what it might do (`Continue`). When in `soft-warn` or `suspect`, the button additionally shows the source-of-truth timestamp underneath in mono: `state @ 11:30:42 (47s)`. Operators see exactly what the system is acting on.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:333:The state of the button is computed on every poll; it never lags the underlying conditions.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:341:| missing | unit in plan, no record in state and not derivable as `planned` due to mismatched `plan_ref` | frame contract |
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:342:| extra | unit in state with no plan entry and no `replaces` mapping covering it | `replaces` policy |
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:415:1. Renders only when at least one of these is true: `truth degraded` (parse failure > 60s), `plan ref mismatch`, `state version regression`, `legacy timestamps detected`. Otherwise the strip is absent (zero height — no reserved gap).
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:419:5. The strip never overlaps the swimlane viewport — it adds height to the page chrome above. This is the one piece of vertical real estate the dashboard reserves for "you must read this."
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:421:This honors the no-modal rule (no overlay, no focus trap, no dismissal-required dialog) while preventing severe data integrity issues from being lost in subtle pulse-color shifts.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:437:Filter logic is precise but not self-explanatory. Operators commonly misread "owner=alice AND wave=3" as "either alice or wave 3" and report the dashboard as broken when the intersection is empty. The dashboard makes the math explicit.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:476:| state | treatment |
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:483:| empty (no plan) | minimal empty state: `Drop plan.json` action + `Open file…` button (no illustration) |
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:484:| empty (plan ok, state missing) | swimlanes render planned-only in gray + inline banner `No state file — showing plan only` |
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:492:The dashboard mutates visual state from many independent sources: polling frames, mode toggles, filter changes, selections, hovers, drift-chip clicks, scroll-jumps, animations. Without a single contract, these can race and produce ghost selections, conflicting visibility, mixed-time displays, and pulses landing on vanished nodes. The following rules are normative.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:504:5. Rapid mode toggling (e.g. Default → Spotlight → Diff → Default within 200ms) coalesces. Only the final mode is committed at the end of the burst (300ms debounce). Intermediate states are not painted.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:540:| selected unit removed from plan | selection PERSISTS only if the unit still exists in state (drawer shows `unit no longer in plan` banner from §6); if removed from both, selection becomes null and the drawer shows the previous focused unit's last-good snapshot for 5 seconds with a banner `unit T1.2 vanished from plan and state`, then clears |
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:596:The visual system must hold up under grayscale, colorblindness, glare, zoom-out, and high edge density. The following adjustments apply to the previously-stated tokens and glyphs.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:600:Both states are blue and both glyphs read as "circular busy thing" at 16px. Distinction strengthened on three independent axes:
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:602:| state | hue | glyph | motion | top accent |
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:643:The silhouette set is hand-picked so each is distinct at 16px without color: ring vs dashed-ring vs spinner vs check-in-circle vs clock vs lock vs triangle vs arrow. No two share a basic shape category (open shape vs filled vs angular). Tested with three deuteranopia simulator passes at 100%, 75%, and 50% display saturation — all states remain identifiable.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:680:4. Truth-degraded (>60s parse fail) keeps the 25% desaturation because by then the state is *suspect*, not just *late*; making the colors questionable is the correct signal.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:686:The following conditions occur in real plans and state files. The dashboard handles each explicitly; nothing is allowed to crash or silently degrade.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:732:#### Task deleted from plan but still present in state
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:734:A unit is in `state.taken` or `state.completed` but its plan id is gone (no `replaces` alias either). Handling:
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:738:3. The drawer is reachable via the drift chip; the drawer renders the unit with a banner: `unit no longer in plan — state retained for audit`.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:741:This is the only path where state content is visible without a swimlane card.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:768:`fetch(state.json)` returns 200 but the body is incomplete JSON (a writer atomically replaced the file mid-read on a non-atomic filesystem, or the writer wrote in chunks).
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:773:2. Three consecutive parse failures within 6 seconds bumps the heartbeat dot to amber and surfaces a chip `state file unstable — n/3 parses failed` in the heartbeat ticker.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:774:3. After 60s of sustained parse failures (truth-degraded threshold), the persistent degraded-data strip activates with the reason `state.json — parse failure for 60s`.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:775:4. A single isolated parse failure during otherwise healthy polling does NOT trigger any UI change beyond a debug log entry.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:777:#### Heartbeat alive but state unchanged (silent orchestrator stall)
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:779:The poll loop receives valid responses every 2s, the JSON parses cleanly, but `state_version` never advances and no unit's `lastUpdatedAt` changes. The orchestrator is stuck without crashing.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:783:1. The dashboard tracks `framesSinceProgress` — the count of consecutive accepted frames where neither `state_version`, the set of `taken` keys, the set of `completed` keys, nor any `verification.*.ran_at` advanced.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:797:4. The summary bar shows `Idle` health pill and the swimlanes render an empty-state card: `No units in plan — open a plan with at least one unit to begin`.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:819:| `high` | both plan-side and state-side fields required for that bucket are present |
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:820:| `partial` | one side present, the other absent (e.g. plan declares `expected_artifacts` but state record has no `actual_artifacts` block at all) |
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:834:Status flicker under polling races is a UI failure even when the underlying logic is correct. The compare layer adds two stabilization rules.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:838:Once a unit derives `complete`, `failed`, or `skipped` (terminal states), the dashboard requires two consecutive non-terminal frames to revert it. A single transient `running` reading sandwiched between two `complete` readings does not unflag the unit. This handles the race where a writer briefly re-stages a `taken` entry for a unit that was already in `completed`.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:840:The hysteresis is bounded: after 30s of sustained non-terminal status the unit reverts unconditionally. Stuck terminal states cannot persist indefinitely.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:844:Each `ComparedView` carries an `acceptedAt: number` (millisecond epoch from the dashboard clock) and the underlying `state_version`. The publish-or-discard rule:
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:846:1. If `state_version` is present and ≤ the last accepted frame's `state_version`, discard. The previous frame stays on screen.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:847:2. If `state_version` is absent, fall back to monotonic `acceptedAt` ordering — but raise a warning chip in the heartbeat strip: `state version missing — frame ordering unverified`.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:848:3. If `state_version` jumps backward more than 1 (e.g. 5 → 2), assume a fresh state file replaced an older one (rollback or restore); accept the new value as a new baseline and log a warning chip.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:858:| `deps-topology` | the plan's declared `depends_on` set differs from a prior plan revision's set for the same unit ID | only when `plan_version` advances and the prior plan is in cache or `replaces` mappings reveal it |
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:859:| `deps-runtime` | satisfaction state diverges from declared topology — e.g. the plan declares `T1.2` depends on `T1.1`, but state shows `T1.2` running while `T1.1` is `failed` | every poll |
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:861:The drift panel's `deps` bucket is split into two sub-rows under one header. Most operational drift is `deps-runtime`; `deps-topology` only matters during plan revisions and surfaces only then. The compare layer emits separate entries; the UI groups them under one collapsible parent for visual economy.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:863:`deps-runtime` confidence is always `high` (both sides are present by construction). `deps-topology` confidence is `partial` when the prior plan is unavailable.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:885:1. **Writer clock authority**: the most recent timestamp written by `state` (file mtime as fallback when no timestamp exists in the record) is the dashboard's clock reference for that frame. The dashboard never compares its own wall clock against a writer's timestamp for ordering.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:886:2. **Skew tolerance**: when a unit's `started_at` is later than its `finished_at`, the dashboard logs a `clockSkew` warning on `UnitView.warnings` but renders the unit normally; the timeline displays "skewed" in the drawer's middle stratum.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:888:4. **Monotonic event sequence (future)**: if and when state files include an `event_seq` integer per record, that field overrides timestamps for ordering and removes all clock dependence. The dashboard will pick up `event_seq` automatically when present; it is documented in the state schema as an optional field for the next revision.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:895:The current waveplan plan and state schemas do not encode several facts the dashboard treats as primary signal. Rather than fabricate that signal, this design declares the schema fields it requires and the contract under which the dashboard reads them. Schema extensions are listed here so they can be planned and merged before or alongside the dashboard implementation.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:920:| `state_version` | root | integer, monotonic | Frame contract |
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:921:| `state_generation` | root | string | Frame contract |
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:922:| `plan_ref` | root | `{ plan_version, plan_generation }` | Pairs state to the plan it derived from |
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:940:Plan and state files mutate independently and may be observed mid-write. To prevent mixed-frame truth, the dashboard treats every render as a paired snapshot.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:942:1. The compare layer reads `plan_version` + `plan_generation` and `state.plan_ref` on every poll.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:943:2. If `state.plan_ref` does not match the loaded plan, the state is considered out-of-frame. The dashboard renders the last in-frame `ComparedView` and shows a thin amber banner: `state pinned to plan v{n}, current plan is v{m}`.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:944:3. A new `ComparedView` is published only when both files parse, both versions match, and `state_version` increased monotonically.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:945:4. If `state_version` regresses (file replaced or rolled back), the dashboard discards its last-good frame and refreshes from the new baseline.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:951:The current state schema declares `YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM` timestamps without timezone or seconds. The dashboard requires:
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:954:- The compare layer accepts the legacy `YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM` format and parses it as local time with seconds set to `00`. A migration warning surfaces in the heartbeat strip if any timestamp uses the legacy form: `mixed timestamp formats — promote state file to ISO 8601`.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:967:3. The compare layer treats `replaces` as identity continuity: state entries keyed to a replaced ID are reattributed to the replacement unit without raising `missing` or `extra`.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:968:4. Splits (one old → many new) attribute the state record to the first new unit and surface a non-fatal `split` chip in the drift `extra` bucket as informational, not error.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:969:5. Merges (many old → one new) accept any one of the prior IDs as the state key during a transition window.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:977:- `state.json` — conforms to `docs/specs/waveplan-state-schema.json` (with extensions above).
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:978:- optional event log / heartbeat source (poll interval 1–5s, or push-driven).
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:984:loadState(stateJson) → IndexedState { taken, completed, reviews, owners, timestamps }
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:985:compare(plan, state) → ComparedView { units: UnitView[], drift: DriftReport, metrics: Metrics }
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:1003:Terminal states win over in-flight states. Order of precedence, top wins:
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:1023:The state schema permits multiple concurrent entries in `taken`. The dashboard treats the active set as plural and the drawer as a focus selector, not a singular truth.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:1049:| `totalTasks` | — | — | count of `units` in `IndexedPlan`; extra-in-state units are counted separately as `extraTasks`, never folded in |
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:1054:| `extraTasks` | state entries with no plan id and no `replaces` alias | — | always non-negative; surfaces in the summary bar when > 0 |
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:1072:| state | Zustand or React context + reducer (no need for Redux scale) |
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:1171:The dashboard ships when all of the following are true with sample plan + state covering every required schema extension:
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:1179:7. Stopping the state-file poll for >15s drives the heartbeat strip to red and desaturates nodes; resuming restores instantly.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:1180:8. Orthogonal edges never overlap node cards and use the correct color and dash style for their dependency state.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:1183:11. **Frame contract**: when state's `plan_ref` does not match the loaded plan, the dashboard pins the last in-frame view and surfaces the version-mismatch banner; rendering never mixes plan v_n with state targeting v_m.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:1189:17. **Verification authority**: removing the `verification.tests` block from sample state drops the tests tile to `no data`; no synthesized count appears.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:1190:18. **Identity continuity**: a plan revision that renames `T1.2` → `T1.5` with `replaces: ["T1.2"]` reattributes the prior state record without raising `missing` or `extra` drift.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:1191:19. **Timestamp tolerance**: a state file mixing legacy `YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM` and ISO 8601 timestamps parses without error and surfaces the `mixed timestamp formats` warning in the heartbeat strip.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:1213:41. **Next Action button gating**: forcing a state file 47s old produces the soft-warn underline + confirmation toast on click; forcing > 60s parse failure locks the button (no-op click + tooltip).
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:1221:49. **Out-of-order discard**: posting state version 5 then 4 (in that order) leaves the version-5 view on screen; the heartbeat strip does not log an update for version 4.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:1222:50. **State version absent warning**: removing `state_version` from the fixture surfaces a `state version missing — frame ordering unverified` chip in the heartbeat strip.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:1223:51. **Dependency sub-buckets**: the drift panel's `deps` bucket renders two sub-rows (`runtime` and `topology`); a fixture with a runtime mismatch surfaces under `runtime` only, and `topology` reads `0`.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:1225:53. **Timestamp skew**: a unit with `started_at` later than `finished_at` renders normally but logs `clockSkew` in `UnitView.warnings` and shows `skewed` in the drawer middle stratum on hover.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:1226:54. **Denominator rules verified**: with 10 plan units and 1 extra-in-state unit, `progressPercent = completedTasks / 10` and the summary bar shows `(+1 extra)` chip; the drift `extra` bucket reports the unit; `dependencyReadiness` does not include the extra unit.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:1231:59. **Deleted task in state**: a fixture where state has `T9.9` but plan does not produces an `extra` drift entry; the drawer is reachable via the chip and shows `unit no longer in plan` banner; the card does not render in any swimlane.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:1234:62. **Truncated state file**: feeding a partial-write JSON 3 times in 6s surfaces the `state file unstable` chip; recovers automatically when the next parse succeeds.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:1235:63. **Silent stall detection**: a fixture with one `running` unit whose state never changes for 30s surfaces `no progress 0:30 · 1 units running` chip; at 120s the health pill adds `Stalled`.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:1236:64. **Empty plan div-zero**: a plan with zero units shows `—%` progress, `Idle` health pill, and an empty-state card; no `NaN` anywhere in the DOM.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:1248:76. **Frame-bound transforms**: rapid mode toggling (Default → Spotlight → Diff → Default within 200ms) commits only the final mode after a 300ms debounce; intermediate states are not painted; verified via `window.__waveplan.metrics.modeCommits` counting one per burst.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:1252:80. **Selection vanishes gracefully**: removing `T2.1` from both plan and state shows the prior focused snapshot with a `unit T2.1 vanished from plan and state` banner for 5s, then clears selection — never crashes.

